[SN]TITLE[SN]
International friendly: Slovakia U21 4-0 Scotland U21

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland Under-21s fell to a heavy defeat against Slovakia in Wednesday's friendly in Myjava - a third loss in three games for coach Scot Gemmill.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Albert Rusnak struck to put the hosts ahead early in the match.
An Alex Iacovitti own goal doubled their advantage and Branislav Ninaj netted the home side's third.
Filip Balaj rounded off victory for Slovakia, who will feature at next year's European Under-21 Championship in Poland.
Hamilton Academical's Eamonn Brophy won his first Scotland Under-21 cap in the starting line-up while substitutes Alan Forrest, of Ayr United, and Morton's Jai Quitongo also debuted for the side.
Gemmill replaced Ricky Sbragia in September and oversaw 2-0 defeats by Iceland and Macedonia at the end of Scotland's unsuccessful European Championship qualifying campaign.
